node.text:
Tom Brady has already cemented his legacy as one of the greatest to ever play the game and the legendary quarterback says he's got many more years left in him. He was asked a question that people often search on Google: "Can Tom Brady play until 50 years old?" Brady replied: "I don't find it so difficult. Plus, in Florida, it's kind of a retiree state, so I feel like I can play and then just glide into retirement. I think I can. I think it's a yes."⁠
⁠
(📸: AP Images)⁠

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNN on September 17, 2021. May be an image of outdoors and text that says 'FDA advisers recommend booster for people 65 and older and those at high risk FDA U.S. Department of Health and Human Services Food and Drug Administration CNN BREAKING NEWS'.

node.text:
Vaccine advisers to the FDA have voted unanimously to recommend emergency use authorization of a booster dose of Pfizer’s vaccine six months after full vaccination in people 65 and older and those at high risk of severe Covid-19. The advisers also rejected a broader application to approve the use of booster doses of Pfizer’s vaccines in everyone 16 and older six months after they are fully vaccinated.⁠
⁠
(📸: Ting Shen/Xinhua/Getty Images)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNN on September 17, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'The US military admits it killed 10 civilians and targeted the wrong vehicle in a Kabul airstrike The top general of US Central Command said the strike was a "mistake" and offered an apology. CNN BREAKING NEWS'.

node.text:
A US military investigation into a deadly Kabul drone strike in August has found that it killed 10 civilians and the driver, and the vehicle targeted was likely not a threat associated with ISIS-K, Gen. Frank McKenzie, the top general of US Central Command announced Friday.⁠
⁠

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNN on September 17, 2021. May be an image of tree, outdoors and text that says 'Officials wrapped the world's largest tree in foil to guard it against California wildfires CNN GENERAL SHERMAN'.

node.text:
The world's largest tree has been wrapped in foil to protect it against flames from a fire raging in California's scenic Sequoia National Park. The tree, called General Sherman, is 275 feet tall, and over 36 feet in diameter at the base, making it taller than the Statue of Liberty from its base to the torch.⁠
⁠
(📸: Sequoia and Kings Canyon National Parks)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNN on September 17, 2021. May be an image of 3 people, people standing, suit and text that says 'Colorado governor weds his partner in the first same-sex marriage for a sitting governor CNN'.

node.text:
Colorado Gov. Jared Polis and his partner of 18 years, Marlon Reis, were married on Wednesday, according to a statement from the governor's office. In 2018, Polis became the first openly gay man elected governor in the United States. He is the second out LGBTQ person elected governor, after Oregon Gov. Kate Brown, according to the LGBTQ Victory Fund.⁠
⁠
(📸: Jocelyn Augustino/AP)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNN on September 17, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Here are 5 countries that are opening up and living with Covid: Denmark Singapore Thailand South Africa Chile CNN'.

node.text:
More than 18 months into the coronavirus pandemic, a number of countries have decided it's time to open up and adopt a "living with Covid" model.⁠
⁠
"The bad news is that Covid-19 may never go away. The good news is that it is possible to live normally with it in our midst," Singapore's top Covid-19 officials wrote in an op-ed.⁠
⁠
Tap the link in our bio to read how these strategies are playing out.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNN on September 16, 2021. May be an image of 3 people and text.

node.text:
Students in a southern Pennsylvania school district are protesting a ban on anti-racism books and resources. Last October, the all-White school board unanimously banned a list of educational resources that included a children's book about Rosa Parks, Malala Yousafzai's autobiography and CNN's Sesame Street town hall on racism.⁠
⁠
(📸: Linh Tran/CNN)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNN on September 16, 2021. May be an image of 2 people and text that says 'One of of US oldest cities has had only White men as mayors. In November, that changes CNN'.

node.text:
Boston is poised to make history in November with two women of color competing for a mayoral seat that has been occupied by White men for the past 200 years. City Councilors Michelle Wu and Annissa Essaibi George claimed the two top spots in Tuesday’s primary.⁠
⁠
(📸: AP/Getty Images)⁠

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNN on September 16, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Federal officers will now be banned from using chokeholds and no-knock warrants in the latest nationwide push for more police accountability CNN'.

node.text:
Federal law enforcement officers will be banned from using neck restraints (commonly known as chokeholds) during arrests and using no-knock entries while executing warrants except in rare cases, the Justice Department announced Tuesday. This addresses two aspects of police accountability under federal jurisdiction, but state and local governments have already made these changes over the past two years.⁠
⁠
